<p>Survey Code: <span class="blue">251T</span></p>

<p class="red"><strong>PLEASE COMPLETE AT MOST ONE <span class="blue">251T</span> SURVEY. YOU WILL NOT BE PAID FOR COMPLETING MORE THAN ONE SURVEY WITH THIS CODE.</strong></p>

<h3>Instructions</h3>

<p>This questionnaire presents 8 English sentences. Your task is to decide how natural each sentence sounds. You might not be utterring the sentences by yourself, but you might nevertheless have an intuition as to how natural they are. Please indicate how natural the sentence sounds by selecting one of the buttons below the sentence, where 1 is most unnatural and 3 is most natural. Here is an example:</p>

<div class="trial">
	
	<p>I don't know whether Paul will go to the party because Paul doesn't like parties.</p>

	<table><tbody>
		<tr>
			<td><label for="ChoiceSample1-1">1</label></td>
			<td><label for="ChoiceSample1-2">2</label></td>
			<td><label for="ChoiceSample1-3">3</label></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><input type="radio" id="ChoiceSample1-1" name="ChoiceSample1" value="1" /></td>
			<td><input type="radio" id="ChoiceSample1-2" name="ChoiceSample1" value="2" /></td>
			<td><input type="radio" id="ChoiceSample1-3" name="ChoiceSample1" value="3" /></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>
</div>

<p>In the above example, it is very clear that the sentence is natural, so please select the button under 3.</p>

<p>Here is another example:</p>

<div class="trial">
	
	<p>I don't know whether Paul will go to the party because Paul likes parties.</p>

	<table><tbody>
		<tr>
			<td><label for="ChoiceSample2-1">1</label></td>
			<td><label for="ChoiceSample2-2">2</label></td>
			<td><label for="ChoiceSample2-3">3</label></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><input type="radio" id="ChoiceSample2-1" name="ChoiceSample2" value="1" /></td>
			<td><input type="radio" id="ChoiceSample2-2" name="ChoiceSample2" value="2" /></td>
			<td><input type="radio" id="ChoiceSample2-3" name="ChoiceSample2" value="3" /></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>
</div>

<p>In this case you would probably feel that the sentence is unnatural. So please choose the button on the left, like 1 or 2.</p>

<p class="red"><strong>In order to get paid, please make sure that you answer all 8 questions.</strong></p>

<div style='border: 1px solid black'>

<p><strong>Consent Statement</strong></p>

<p>We invite you to participate in a research study on language production and comprehension. This study is conducted by Ang Li at the Department of Linguistics, New York University.</p>

<p>We will ask you to do a linguistic task such as reading sentences or words, naming pictures or describing scenes, watching videos, making up sentences of your own, or participating in a simple language game.</p>

<p>By participating in this study, you confirm that you are at least 18 years old.</p>

<p>If you continue, understand that your participation in this experiment is voluntary and you have the right to withdraw your consent or discontinue participation at any time. However, please note that if you withdraw before completing the study, no data will be transmitted to the server and you will not receive payment, as we have no way of verifying that you have participated at all. We estimate completion of the experiment to take approximately 5 minutes. There are no risks or benefits of any kind associated with participation in this study. You will be paid for your participation at the posted rate.
Your participation in this study will remain confidential. We are not collecting any personally identifiable information aside from your MTurk Worker ID. Your individual privacy will be maintained in all published and written data resulting from the study. In case we publish raw data or share them with other researchers, your MTurk Worker ID will be removed from the dataset, obscured, or modified. You may print this declaration for your records.</p>

<p>If you have questions about this study, please feel free to email Ang Li at ang.li.aimee@gmail.com. For questions about your rights as a research participant, you may contact the University Committee on Activities Involving Human Subjects, New York University, 665 Broadway, Suite 804, New York, NY 10012 at 212-998-4808 or ask.humansubjects@nyu.edu:</p>

<p><strong>I have read and understood the consent statement. I am at least 18 years of age and a native speaker of English.</strong></p>

